## Isolated per-session environment

Every run executes in its own isolated env ŌĆö own worktree + port + DB + Odoo ŌĆö so
parallel pipeline sessions never collide and the user's main env
(`src/{{ custom_repo_name }}` / `develop` / `odoo.service` / 1669) is untouched. **The model,
scripts and gotchas live in the `worktree-env` skill ŌĆö read it.** What the pipeline
needs from it:

- **Phase 1** runs `wt-start.sh <slug>` and captures its output as `<WT>` (worktree
  path), `<CONF>` (session `odoo.conf`), `<URL>` (browser URL), `<DB>`, `<PORT>`.
  Re-running `wt-start.sh <slug>` refreshes the env (idempotent).
- **Phases 2ŌĆō5** edit/test/PR using those: `git -C <WT> ŌĆ”`, `odoo -c <CONF> ŌĆ”`,
  browser `<URL>`. All code/git happens in `<WT>`, never in `src/{{ custom_repo_name }}`.
- **Phase 6** does NOT tear the env down on its own ŌĆö the worktree is kept so
  the task can continue. `wt-stop.sh <slug>` runs ONLY when the user says the
  session is finished, and only after you ask (see Phase 6 Step 0 /
  `feedback_never_auto_drop_worktree`).
- The odoo MCP can verify a session too ŌĆö `connect` to it explicitly (`host="localhost"`,
  `port=<PORT>`, `database=<DB>`, `admin`/`admin`); the `default`/`prod` profiles are
  `develop`/prod, so pass explicit params, not a profile. The connection is global per
  MCP server ŌĆö alternate deliberately with prod ticket ops (`odoo-tickets`) and check
  `get_connection_status`.
- Prereq: a seed dump in `backup/` ({% if backup_s3_bucket %}`nix run .#download-backup` to fetch/refresh{% else %}drop a `pg_dump -Fc` file in manually{% endif %}) ŌĆö
  if `wt-start` reports none, ask the user to provide it first.

