### Phase 3: QC Gate (review + validation, loops back to dev)

The quality gate. Two checks run here; either one failing sends the code back to `dev`, then the gate re-runs. **Max 3 fix iterations.** This is the only quality gate ŌĆö the code is reviewed here, before the PR, so the PR is clean and there is no post-PR review round.

**Check 1 ŌĆö code review.** Spawn the **`review`** subagent (local-diff mode):

> <PROJECT_RULES_BLOB>
>
> Review ONLY these changed files (local diff, not a PR): <LIST OF CHANGED FILES>.
> They live in the worktree `<WT>` ŌĆö read them there and diff with
> `git -C <WT> diff` (not the user's main checkout `src/{{ custom_repo_name }}`).
> Your goal here is COVERAGE: report every issue you find ŌĆö including low-severity
> ones and ones you are unsure about ŌĆö each tagged with a severity (CRITICAL /
> MAJOR / MINOR) and a confidence (high / medium / low). Cover TEST COVERAGE too:
> flag missing tests for computed fields, constraints, state transitions, access
> rights, error branches, and the regression case (old behavior still works).
> Do not self-filter; this orchestrator is the ranking/filter stage.
> review is read-only; your FILES_CHANGED will be "none (read-only)".
> Return OPEN_THREADS for anything worth filing separately, and DECISIONS for
> any judgment calls on severity.

The `review` agent has `style` + `testing` preloaded. It is read-only.

**Check 2 ŌĆö validation.** Run directly (NOT via subagent) ŌĆö you need Chrome browser tools and this session's running Odoo. Everything here targets THIS session (`<CONF>` / `<DB>` / `<URL>`), never the main env or another session.

0. Point the odoo MCP at THIS session for backend checks ŌĆö
   `connect host="localhost" port=<PORT> database="<DB>" username="admin" password="admin"`
   (the `default`/`prod` profiles are `develop`/prod, not a session). Confirm
   `get_connection_status` shows `<DB>` before trusting it. The connection is global,
   so never run session checks while parked on prod, or prod ticket ops while on the
   session.
1. Refresh the env (picks up any module added during dev) and stop its Odoo:
   ```bash
   bash "${{ project_dir_var }}/.claude/skills/worktree-env/scripts/wt-start.sh" <slug>
   systemctl --user stop odoo-wt@<slug>.service
   ```
   (only THIS session's Odoo stops; the user's `odoo.service` and other sessions
   keep running)
2. Update and run tests against this session:
   ```bash
   odoo -c <CONF> -u <MODULE_NAME> \
       --workers 0 --test-enable --test-tags /<MODULE_NAME> \
